author: Gamers Nexus
description:
Sponsor: Thermaltake TR100 mini-ITX Travel Case on Amazon https://geni.us/Yn9DXb
We bought the NVIDIA RTX PRO 6000 Blackwell Workstation Edition for review and benchmarks totally independently of NVIDIA. In this review and benchmark suite of the RTX PRO 6000, we test the card for gaming performance on an AMD Ryzen 9800X3D (mostly to see if there's still scaling room), our first suite of LLM benchmarks with LM Studio, and we run thermals and acoustics. The review also includes a tear-down of the RTX PRO 6000 with comparisons vs. the NVIDIA RTX 5090 Founders Edition.

Our source we bought this card from operates a custom PC building website: https://veratu.com/
